# The Book List- (Courtesy of Red Team Journal & Red Teams.Net)
1. Team of Teams by General (Ret.) Stanley McChrystal 
2. Field Command by Charles "Sid" Heal
3. Billion Dollar Lessons: What You Can Learn from the Most Inexcusable Business Failures of the Last 25 Years, Paul Carroll and Chunka Mui
4. How Google Works (2014), Eric Schmidt and Jonathan Rosenberg
5. Let My People Go Surfing: The Education of a Reluctant Businessman (2006), Yvon Chouinard
6. The Seventh Sense (2016), Joshua Cooper Ramo
7. Zero to One: Notes on Startups, or How to Build the Future (2014), Peter Thiel with Blake Masters
8. Brave New War: The Next Stage of Terrorism and the End of Globalization (2008), John Robb
9. Dirty Wars: The World Is a Battlefield (2014), Jeremy Scahill
10. Human Intelligence, Counterterrorism, and National Leadership: A Practical Guide (2008), Gary Berntsen
11. Red Teams and Counterterrorism Training (2011), Stephen Sloan and Robert J. Bunker
12. The Art of Deception: Controlling the Human Element of Security (2003), Kevin Mitnick
13. The Art and Science of Military Deception (2013), Hal Rothstein and Barton Whaley
14. Practise to Deceive: Learning Curves of Military Deception Planners (2016), Barton Whaley
15. Unweaving the Web: Deception and Adaptation in Future Urban Operations (2002), Scott Gerwehr and Russell W. Glenn (Also available to download from the RAND website.)
16. The Applied Critical Thinking Handbook, 7.0, TRADOC
17. Black Box Thinking: Why Most People Never Learn from Their Mistakes—But Some Do (2015),
   Matthew Syed
18. Creativity, Inc.: Overcoming the Unseen Forces that Stand in the Way of True Inspiration (2014), Ed Catmull
19. Red Teaming: How Your Business Can Conquer the Competition by Challenging Everything (2017), Bryce Hoffman
20. Risk Savvy: How to Make Good Decisions (2014), Gerd Gigerenzer
21. Shortcut: How Analogies Reveal Connections, Spark Innovation, and Sell Our Greatest Ideas (2015), John Pollack
22. Superforecasting: The Art and Science of Prediction (2015), Philip E. Tetlock and Dan Gardner
23. The Art of Intelligence: Lessons from a Life in the CIA’s Clandestine Service (2013), Henry A. Crumpton
24. Man in the Shadows: Inside the Middle East Crisis with a Director of Israel’s Mossad (2006), Efraim Halevy
25. Open Source Intelligence Techniques, 5th edition (2016), Michael Bazzell
26. Silent Warfare: Understanding the World of Intelligence, 3rd editon (2002), Abram N. Shulsky
27. Spies Against Armageddon: Inside Israel’s Secret Wars, 2nd edition (2014), Dan Raviv and Yossi Melman
28. The Volunteer: The Incredible True Story of an Israeli Spy on the Trail of International Terrorists (2011), Michael Ross with Jonathan Kay
29. Five Years to Freedom: The True Story of a Vietnam POW (1984), James Rowe
30. Out of Captivity: Surviving 1,967 Days in the Colombian Jungle, Marc Gonsalves, Keith Stansell, and Tom Howes with Gary Brozek
31. Phantom Soldier: The Enemy’s Answer to U.S. Firepower (2001), H. John Poole
32. Tactics of the Crescent Moon: Militant Muslim Combat Methods (2004), H. John Poole
33. The Tiger’s Way: A U.S. Private’s Best Chance for Survival (2003), H. John Poole
34. Brotherhood of Warriors: Behind Enemy Lines with a Commando in One of the World’s Most Elite Counterterrorism Units (2009), Aaron Cohen and Douglas Century
35. Chosen Soldier (2008), Dick Couch
36. Inside Delta Force: The Story of America’s Elite Counterterrorist Unit (2007), Eric Haney
37. Killer Elite: The Inside Story of America’s Most Secret Special Operations Team (2007), Michael Smith
38. Left of Bang: How the Marine Corps’ Combat Hunter Program Can Save Your Life (2014), Patrick Van Horne
39. The Mission, the Men, and Me: Lessons from a Former Delta Force Commander (2010), Pete Blaber
40. Navy SEAL Sniper: An Intimate Look at the Sniper of the 21st Century (2017), Glen Doherty and Brandon Webb
41. Relentless Strike: The Secret History of the Joint Special Operations Command (2016), Sean Naylor
42. Secret Warriors: Inside the Covert Military Operations of the Reagan Era (1988), Steven Emerson
43. Powerful Peace: A Navy SEAL’s Lessons on Peace from a Lifetime at War (2012), J. Robert DuBois
44. The Red Circle (2014), Brandon Webb
45. 1493: Uncovering the New World Columbus Created (2012), Charles C. Mann
46. Emergency: This Book Will Save Your Life (2009), Neil Strauss
47. The Martian (2011), Andy Weir
48. A More Beautiful Question: The Power of Inquiry to Spark Breakthrough Ideas (2016), Warren Berger
49. On Bullshit (2005), Harry G. Frankfurt
50. The Rock Warrior’s Way: Mental Training for Climbers (2006), Arno Ilgner
51. Trying Not to Try: Ancient China, Modern Science, and the Power of Spontaneity (2015), Edward Slingerland
52. What Got You Here Won’t Get You There: How Successful People Become Even More Successful (2007), Marshall Goldsmith
53. The Science of Social Influence: Advances and Future Progress (2007), Anthony Pratkanis (academic and informative)
54. Techniques of Social Influence: The Psychology of Gaining Compliance (2015), Dariusz Dolinski
55. Social Engineering: The Art of Human Hacking (2010), Christopher Hadnagy
56. Just Listen: Discover the Secret of Getting Through to Absolutely Anyone (2015), Mark Goulston
57. KODO: Ancient Ways: Lessons in the Spiritual Life of the Warrior/Martial Artist (1996), Kensho Furuya
58. Deciphering Sun Tzu: How to Read the Art of War (2014), Derek M. C. Yuen
59. The Future of Strategy (2015), Colin Gray
60. The Unfettered Mind: Writings from a Zen Master to a Master Swordsman (2012), Takuan Soho, translated by William Scott Wilson
61. The Art of War: Sun Zi’s Military Methods (2008), translated by Victor H. Mair
62. The Essence of Aikido: Spiritual Teachings of Morihei Ueshiba, compiled by John Stevens
63. The Kautiliya Arthashastra (2014), translated by R. P. Kangle
64. The Book of Five Rings (ca. 1645), Miyamoto Musashi
65. Escape the Wolf: Preemptive Personal Security Handbook for the Traveling Professional (2012), Clinton Emerson with Lynn Walters
66. Schneier on Security (2008), Bruce Schneier
67. Red Team: How to Succeed by Thinking Like the Enemy (2015), Micah Zenko
68. A Burglar’s Guide to the City (2016), Geoff Manaugh
69. Practical Lock Picking: A Physical Penetration Tester’s Training Guide (2010), Deviant Ollam
70. The Art of Intrusion: The Real Stories Behind the Exploits of Hackers, Intruders, and Deceivers (2005), Kevin Mitnick
71. The Practice Of Network Security Monitoring (2013), Richard Bejtlich
72. Hacking: The Art of Exploitation, 2nd Edition (2008), Jon Erickson
73. Hacking Exposed 7: Network Security Secrets and Solutions, Stuart McClure, Joe Scambray, and George Kurtz
74. Metasploit: The Penetration Tester’s Guide (2011), David Kennedy, Jim O’Gorman, Devon Kearns, and Mati Aharoni
75. Nmap Network Scanning: The Official Nmap Project Guide to Network Discovery and Security Scanning (2009), Gordon “Fyodor” Lyon
76. Rtfm: Red Team Field Manual (2014), Ben Clark
77. The Shellcoder’s Handbook: Discovering and Exploiting Security Holes, 2nd Edition (2007), Chris Anley, John Heasman, Felix “FX” Linder, Gerardo Richarte
78. Snort IDS and IPS Toolkit (Jay Beale’s Open Source Security) (2007), Jay Beale, Andrew Baker, Joel Esler, et al.
79. Unauthorised Access: Physical Penetration Testing For IT Security Teams (2009), Wil Allsopp
80. Violent Python: A Cookbook for Hackers, Forensic Analysts, Penetration Testers and Security Engineers (2012), TJ O’Connor


